\subsection{ RC time-constant circuit}
 
\medskip \centerline{\includegraphics{01018.eps}} 
 

For DC analysis, the initial conditions of any reactive component (C or L) must be specified (voltage for capacitors, current for inductors).  This is provided by the last data field of each capacitor card (\texttt{ic=0}).  To perform a DC analysis, the \texttt{.tran} ("\textit{transient}") analysis option must be specified, with the first data field specifying time increment in seconds, the second specifying total analysis timespan in seconds, and the "\texttt{uic}" telling it to "use initial conditions" when analyzing.
 

